data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider allowed synchronous LINQ operations (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) via an explicit opt-in flag that performed sync-over-async internally. **In .NET 11, that opt-in is removed entirely.** Calling any synchronous query or save method on the Cosmos provider now throws an `InvalidOperationException`.

## All four methods break:

| Method | Throws because |
|--------|---------------|
| `ToList()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `First()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `Count()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `SaveChanges()` | Sync save removed |

## Fix: Convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

The Cosmos DB provider's underlying SDK is fully async — .NET 11 removes the sync façade entirely, so there's no workaround other than going async all the way up the call stack.
